@node features "Features"

                               Features

-Easy installation: just run the game and play!

-100 different game patterns to play with.

-UkooBar is a "Workbench" game, so it is meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically be
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-UkooBar works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first
version of this game.

1.0: -First public release.

1.1: Some changes have been made to the program code:
      -Now the game has 100 different game boards to play with.
      -A 'Colour' button has been added, this allows the player to choose
       the colour that surrounds the bars when they are properly aligned.
      -Various other enhancements have been made.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "UkooBar" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 4
colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any octagonal-shaped tile. If there are bars surrounding
it, either horizontally or vertically, and they are not aligned with the
tile, they will rotate by 90 degrees toward that tile. The bars that are
already aligned to the tile will not move. If a bar is correctly aligned, a
coloured rectangle will surround it.

  When all bars are correctly aligned (all bars are surrounded by coloured
rectangles), UkooBar will show how many moves it took to complete the game
pattern, and then it will display another pattern to play with.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS
-------

  In the game window, the following buttons appear:

@{b}Replay@{ub}: Reshuffles the current game pattern.

@{b}Colour@{ub}: Changes the colour of the rectangles surrounding the bars.

@{b}'?'@{ub}:    Briefly displays the pattern to match.

@{b}About@{ub}:  Displays the informations about the game.

@endnode

